od's forthcoming projects. Agents are crucial to understanding how creative and economic power are intertwined in Hollywood today. They play a key role in the process by which artistic worth and economic value are evaluated and attributed to people and projects. Roussel's fieldwork examines what "having relationships" really means for agents, and how they perform the relationship work that's at the heart of their professional existence and success. Representing Talent helps us to understand the players behind the definition of entertainment itself, as well as behind its current transformations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aMotion picture industryzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aTheatrical agencies - California - History. 0aTheatrical agencieszCaliforniaxHistory. 0aTheatrical agentszCaliforniaxHistory. 4aHollywood. 4aartistic careers. 4acultural brokerage. 4acultural markets. 4acultural sociology. 4afilm production. 4asocial networks. 4asociology of work. 4atalent agencies. 4atalent agents. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226487137423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226487137.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles